	<h2><a name="join_course"></a>Join a Course</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Click the "Add Course" button from the navigational menu.</li>
			<li class="optional">Search for a key term from the course using the search bar.</li>
			<li>Click the "Join" button to the left of the desired course.</li>
		</ul>
	
	<h2><a name="add_course"></a>Create a Course</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Click the "Add Course" button from the navigational menu.</li>
			<li class="optional">Check if your class already exists by using the search bar.</li>
			<li>Click the "Create New Course" link at the bottom of the page.</li>
			<li>Enter your course's information into the creation form.</li>
			<ul>
				<li class="required">Title, Identifier, Credits, and Start/End Date for the Course.</li>
				<li class="optional">Section, School, Professor, Description, and the start/end dates help others join the correct course.</li>
			</ul>
			<li>Add Assignment Types to quickly generate Homework, Quizzes, Exams ...</li>
			<li>Click "Create Course" at the bottom of the page.</li>
		</ul>

	<h2><a name="edit_course"></a>Edit a Course</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>After a Course has been selected click the "Edit" link in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Change the fields you wish to edit and click the "Update Course" button when you are finished.</li>
		</ul>

	<h2><a name="edit_grade_scale"></a>Edit the Grade Scale</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>After a Course has been selected click the "Edit Grade Scale" link in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Expand the grade scale and edit the information.</li>
			<li>Click the "Update Grade Scale" button when finished.</li>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="grade_assignment"></a>Grade an Assignment</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Find the Assignment you wish to grade in the "Upcoming" or "Past" tab.</li>
			<li>Option 1 (short way)</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Click the dropdown arrow for the corresponding assignment.</li>
				<li>Enter your grade and click "Save".</li>
			</ul>
			<li>Option 2 (long way)</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Select the Assignment.</li>
				<li>Click "Add Grade"/"Edit Grade" in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
				<li>Enter your grade and click "Create Grade"/"Update Grade" when finished.</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
	
	<h2><a name="add_assignment"></a>Add an Assignment</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Click the "Add Assignment" link in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Edit the information you wish to change and click the "Create Assignment" button when finished.</li>
			<ul>
				<li class="required">Name, Assignment Type, and Worth must be a number for the Assignment.</li>
				<li class="optional">Description and Due Date can aid in course management.</li>
			</ul>
			<li class="optional">Multiple Assignments can be quickly generated when creating a new Assignment Type.</li>
		</ul>
	
	<h2><a name="edit_assignment"></a>Edit an Assignment</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Find the Assignment you wish to edit in the "Upcoming" or "Past" tab.</li>
			<li>Option 1 (short way)</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Click the dropdown arrow for the corresponding assignment.</li>
				<li>Click the "Edit Info" button.</li>
				
			</ul>
			<li>Option 2 (long way)</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Select the Assignment.</li>
				<li>Click the "Edit" link in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			</ul>
			<li>Edit the information you wish to change and click the "Update Assignment" button when finished.</li>
			<ul>
				<li class="required">Name, Assignment Type, and Worth for the Assignment, and the Worth must be a number.</li>
				<li class="optional">Description and Due Date can aid in course management.</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="disable_assignment"></a>Disable an Assignment</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Find the Assignment you wish to edit in the "Upcoming" or "Past" tab.</li>
			<li>Click on the dropdown arrow corresponding to the correct Assignment Type.</li>
			<li>Click the "Disable" button. This option will only affect you, but it will <strong>DELETE</strong> the grade for that assignment.</li>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="enable_assignment"></a>Enable an Assignment</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Find the Assignment you wish to edit in the "Upcoming" or "Past" tab.</li>
			<li>Click the "Enable" button. This option will only enable the assignment for you. This option does not retrieve grades that were previously deleted from disabling the Assignment.</li>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="add_assignment_type"></a>Add an Assignment Type</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Click the "Add Assignment Type" link in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Edit the information you wish to change and click the "Create Assignment Type" button when finished.</li>
			<ul>
				<li class="required">Name is the only required field, but a Worth should be given if the Course is not points based.</li>
				<li class="optional">Description can aid in course management.</li>
				<li class="optional">Generate multiple assignments by selecting "Number to Generate". You can also add a worth to all of the generated assignments.
									The assignments will be named Hw 1, Hw 2 ... based on the Assignment Type Name.</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="edit_assignment_type"></a>Edit an Assignment Type</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Click the "Info" link in the "Pages" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Click on the dropdown arrow corresponding to the correct Assignment Type.</li>
			<li class="optional">Edit the Worth and click the "Save" button to quickly change the worth of the Assignment Type.</li>
			<li>Click the "Edit Info" button.</li>
			<li>Edit the information you wish to change and click the "Update Assignment Type" button when finished.</li>
			<ul>
				<li class="required">Name is the only required field, but a Worth should be given if the Course is not points based.</li>
				<li class="optional">Description can aid in course management.</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="disable_assignment_type"></a>Disable an Assignment Type</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Click the "Info" link in the "Pages" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Click on the dropdown arrow corresponding to the correct Assignment Type.</li>
			<li>Click the "Disable" button. This option will only affect you, but it will <strong>DELETE</strong> every grade for every assignment categorized by that Assignment Type.</li>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="enable_assignment_type"></a>Enable an Assignment Type</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Select a Course that you have joined located in the left side navigational menu.</li>
			<li>Click the "Info" link in the "Pages" section of the navigation menu.</li>
			<li>Click the "Enable" button. This option will only enable the assignment type and all assignments under that Assignment Type for you. 
				This option does not retrieve grades that were previously deleted from disabling the Assignment Type.</li>
		</ul>
		
	<h2><a name="edit_personal_information"></a>Edit Personal Information</h2>
		<ul class="steps">
			<li>Option 1 (short way)</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Click on the dropdown arrow next to your name in the upper right hand corner of the web page.</li>
			</ul>
			<li>Option 2 (long way)</li>
				<li>Click on your name in the upper right hand corner of the web page.</li>
				<li>Click the "Edit User Info" link in the "Actions" section of the navigation menu.</li>
