	<h2><a name="courses"></a>Courses</h2>
		<p>Courses are subjects of study in which a student are enrolled. Courses contain an overview of progress and performance for a student.</p>
		<p>Courses can be crated any user. Courses require a Title (name), Identifier, Credits, Start Date, and End Date. The Title and Identifier are used for Class Labels. Credits are used for GPA Prediction and Grade Report. Start and End date are used for hiding old courses.</p>
	
	<h2><a name="assignment_types"></a>Assignment Types</h2>
		<p>Assignment types are simply categories of different assignments. Examples are homework, exams, projects. Assignment types typically carry an overall worth for that category except in the case of a points based course. Points based courses simply add the number of points given to each assignment.</p>
		<p>Assignment types can created by any member of a course. Assignment types only require a Name to identify the category. If the Course for the Assignment Type is not points based a worth should be given.</p>
	
	<h2><a name="assignments"></a>Assignments</h2>
		<p>Assignments are the work that in a course that is graded. Examples are homework #1 do chapter 1 or project 1 etc. Assignments contain grades which tell how a student is performing in a course.</p>
		<p>Assignments can be created by any member of a course. Assignments require a Name and Worth. The name helps identify the assignment. Worth determines how much the assignment affects the course; the worth given must be a number. 
		Description may contain the problems for the assignment, but the description is limited to 144 characters. The due date helps students manage their schedules.</p>
		
	<h2><a name="grades"></a>Grades</h2>
		<p>Grades are specific to users and an assignment. Grades are only visible to the user that created it. Grades help students keep track of their performance in a course.</p>
		<p>Grades can be created by any member of a course.</p>
		
